result.adr_address: The Fleming, 41 Fleming Rd, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: The Fleming, 41 Fleming Rd, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: Osteria Marzia

reviews.text: Visited for the first time for diner with my boyfriend. The food was amazing - highly recommend the fresh pasta and the hamachi! The whole staff was really friendly and helped us ordering. Cherry on the cake was the homemade chocolate ice-cream.

Visited for drinks only. Ordered four cocktails and all were pretty tasty. Alcohol content was acceptable and at 120 dollars or so, seems to be the going rate now for slightly upmarket cocktails. Good ambiance and nice place for a date.
My girlfriend and I had a wonderful evening at Osteria for her birthday.  Our friend Maxwell put us in touch with the manager of Osteria, Tulio and he took great care of us.  Highly recommend!
Great service. Oysters were nice and fresh.  Pasta was excellent. Fish not that fresh though.

You can feel Italy. There many Italian staffs.
The foods are great! I’m Japanese . When I went to this restaurant, I ate oysters from Japan. It was awesome. I felt Japan.
